{"article_id":"rt2W3K9Pzb8I5hGd","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"With the Senate rejecting a House spending bill","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"that included money for President Trump ' s border wall ,","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"the federal government looks headed for a shutdown at midnight .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"The Senate declined to even vote on a short-term spending package","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"containing $ 5 billion of wall funding","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"that the House passed Thursday ,","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"knowing","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"it could not get the 60 votes","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"needed .","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"President Donald Trump ' s sudden refusal","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"to sign anything","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"without wall funding","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"has thrown Congress into a tailspin","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"with just hours","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"to go until a shutdown .","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"The president sent a series of confrontational tweets on Friday morning","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"urging Mitch McConnell to hold a vote on a funding bill","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"sure to fail .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"Then he urged the Senate Majority Leader to \" go nuclear \"","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"and abandon Senate rules","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"to get it done ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"an idea","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"McConnell rejected .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"At issue is Trump ' s red line on $ 5 billion for a border wall , something","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"Democrats universally oppose .","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"The Republican-controlled House passed a bill","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"that includes the $ 5 billion ,","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"but the Senate ,","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"which needs Democrats and Republicans","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"to pass anything","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"needing 60 votes ,","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"is set to reject it .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"The Senate has already passed a bipartisan \" clean \" bill","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"to fund the government into February","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"- without the border money attached .","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"Democrats take control of the House in less than two weeks ,","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"after which it would be much harder for Trump to get his money approved .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"Trump had previously supported the clean-bill plan ,","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"but did an about-face on Thursday after pressure from conservatives .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"With no clear direction","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"on what Trump would be willing to sign ,","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"Congressional leaders are essentially going back to the drawing board .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"\" There is no path forward for the House bill , \"","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"Sen. Jeff Flake","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"( R-AZ )","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"said on the Senate floor Friday night .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"\" What I wanted to do","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"with not proceeding","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"is demonstrate","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"that not all Republicans would be for the House bill either . \"","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"Republican and Democratic leaders of both chambers will now have to hash out a deal with Trump , the person","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"who created the two-day long crisis","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"by going back on his word","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"that he would sign a short-term spending bill","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"even if it didn ' t contain funding for his wall .","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"Trump is staying in DC for the holidays ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"but we don ' t yet know","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"how long these negotiations will take .","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"What we do know","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"is the government is definitely shutting down","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"- at least for some period of time .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"On Friday afternoon , the Senate voted on a motion","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"on whether to take up the House bill","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"including the $ 5 billion in funding for Trump ' s border wall .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"But they never made it to the final vote .","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"Senators of both parties spent Friday scrambling to find a solution to the impasse .","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"At one point , Vice President Mike Pence , incoming Chief of Staff Mick Mulvaney , and senior adviser Jared Kushner paid a visit to Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer and then to House Republicans","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"to try to strike a deal .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"Ultimately , it was to no avail .","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"The Senate passed a short-term spending bill on Wednesday","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"which kept border security funding at current levels ,","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"but the House passed a different version","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"that added in the $ 5 billion in border wall funding","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"the president wanted .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"Trump had seemed to be willing to sign the Senate ' s \" clean \" spending bill earlier this week ,","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"but sharply changed course .","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"The result is that parts of the government are set to shut down at midnight","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"unless there is a dramatic breakthrough .","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"( This bill impacts 25 percent of the government ,","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"the other 75 percent is already funded . )","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"On Friday morning , Trump blamed Democrats for the potential government shutdown","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"and said","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"it could \" last for a very long time . \"","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"The Democrats ,","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"whose votes we need in the Senate ,","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"will probably vote against Border Security and the Wall","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"even though they know","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"it is DESPERATELY NEEDED .","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"If the Dems vote no ,","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"there will be a shutdown","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"that will last for a very long time .","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"People don ' t want Open Borders and Crime !","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"- Donald J. Trump","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"( @ realDonaldTrump )","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"December 21 , 2018","depth":5},{"id":95,"text":"The president ' s focus on Senate passage of the border wall money has even prompted him to call on the upper chamber to use the \" nuclear option , \"","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"which would blow up Senate rules","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"so that the spending bill would only require a simple majority to pass ,","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"instead of the current 60 votes","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"that it needs .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"( Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell has already rejected this idea . )","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"The working assumption that","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"if the government shuts down ,","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"it will one day reopen .","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"At the very least , Democrats will retake the House in January","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"and could pass a new version of the clean Senate bill ,","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"which Trump would be forced to sign or veto .","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"Schumer and House Minority Leader Nancy Pelosi","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"( who is poised to become the next speaker )","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"have made it clear","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"they won ' t agree to $ 5 billion of border wall funding .","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"The question now is whether they will consider a lower sum for border security , potentially in exchange for a deal on immigration reform .","depth":6},{"id":112,"text":"Right now , the number","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"being thrown around","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"is $ 1.6 billion in border security ,","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"but negotiations will likely keep going tonight and possibly through the weekend .","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"Because whatever bill comes up to the Senate needs 60 votes ,","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"which means some Democrats need to support it .","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"Democrats know","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"they have leverage here ,","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"and they will surely demand some concessions","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"( like they have in the past","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"regarding protections for DACA recipients )","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"in exchange .","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"And Trump has motivation","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"to get this done before January 3 ,","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"when the House will change hands","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"and a new Democratic majority","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"that will not cater to his whims","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"takes power .","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"Since roughly three-quarters of the government has been funded by existing bills ,","depth":5},{"id":131,"text":"many services are set to remain intact in the case of a partial shutdown .","depth":5},{"id":132,"text":"Other programs","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"that have been classified as \" essential \"","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"will keep running as well ,","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"although some government entities like museums could see wholesale closures .","depth":5},{"id":136,"text":"Hundreds of thousands of government employees could also be furloughed for the duration of the shutdown ,","depth":4},{"id":137,"text":"though they would likely receive back pay after the fact .","depth":4},{"id":138,"text":"Here ' s a list of what will and won ' t be affected :","depth":6},{"id":139,"text":"Social Security , Medicare , and Medicaid are all slated to keep up their operations uninterrupted .","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"All three programs fall under \" mandatory spending \"","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"that the federal government has committed to","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"and are not affected by the annual appropriations process .","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"( Medicaid also relies , in part , on state spending . )","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"New applicants for these programs might face a wait , however .","depth":7},{"id":145,"text":"Post offices will remain operational","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"and mail delivery will continue .","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"As Rachel Wolfe has written for ,","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"the USPS is funded by independent sources of revenue ,","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"including the sales of products and services -","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"so it ' s not impacted by any kind of shutdown .","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"The Department of Veterans Affairs has already secured its funding ,","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"so veterans hospitals will maintain their routine operations .","depth":9},{"id":153,"text":"Veteran disability pay and GI Bill benefits are funded by their own legislation separate from the annual appropriations bills ,","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"so those would stay consistent ,","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"according to Military.com .","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"People will still be able to get food stamps and subsidized lunches , at least in the short term .","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"But it depends on how long the shutdown lasts :","depth":9},{"id":158,"text":"In the past , the Department of Agriculture has only had limited funding","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"to maintain them","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"without newly approved appropriations .","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"Active-duty members of the military are exempt from shutdown furloughs ,","depth":7},{"id":162,"text":"according to a contingency plan for the Department of Homeland Security .","depth":7},{"id":163,"text":"In the past , Congress has needed to pass separate legislation","depth":8},{"id":164,"text":"to ensure","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"that members of the military are paid in a timely fashion during shutdowns .","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"Otherwise they could potentially see delays in their pay","depth":8},{"id":167,"text":"depending on if the shutdown extends past a certain payment cycle .","depth":8},{"id":168,"text":"While special counsel Robert Mueller ' s investigation into Russian election interference and the Trump campaign is under the purview of the Department of Justice ,","depth":8},{"id":169,"text":"it will not be affected by any appropriations stalemate","depth":8},{"id":170,"text":"since it has its own permanent source of funding ,","depth":7},{"id":171,"text":"CNN reports .","depth":6},{"id":172,"text":"Border security is at the heart of the shutdown fight ,","depth":7},{"id":173,"text":"and a key chunk of the staffing for it is on track to remain intact","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"even in the face of a partial shutdown","depth":9},{"id":175,"text":"involving DHS funding .","depth":9},{"id":176,"text":"US Customs and Border Protection is classified as an \" essential \" service ,","depth":9},{"id":177,"text":"so a majority of its employees are exempt from furloughs during the shutdown","depth":9},{"id":178,"text":"- though they could encounter lags in pay .","depth":8},{"id":179,"text":"As Bloomberg reports ,","depth":8},{"id":180,"text":"\" the overwhelming majority of border patrol , emergency management and immigration enforcement staff would be able to keep doing their jobs , though with their pay delayed . \"","depth":8},{"id":181,"text":"Air traffic controllers ,","depth":8},{"id":182,"text":"who fall under the jurisdiction of the Federal Aviation Administration","depth":9},{"id":183,"text":"( which is under the Transportation Department umbrella ) ,","depth":9},{"id":184,"text":"are deemed \" essential \"","depth":8},{"id":185,"text":"and will keep working during a partial shutdown .","depth":8},{"id":186,"text":"Similarly , Transportation Service Administration agents are also considered \" essential , \"","depth":8},{"id":187,"text":"so airline travel is not expected to see disruptions on this front ,","depth":8},{"id":188,"text":"according to USA Today .","depth":7},{"id":189,"text":"The judiciary is able to maintain operations for a short period of time","depth":9},{"id":190,"text":"after funding runs out","depth":9},{"id":191,"text":"by using money","depth":10},{"id":192,"text":"it ' s gathered from various courts-related fees","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"including \" funds","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"derived from court filings , \"","depth":12},{"id":195,"text":"according to the Congressional Research Service .","depth":9},{"id":196,"text":"In 2018 , the judiciary said","depth":9},{"id":197,"text":"it had the wherewithal","depth":10},{"id":198,"text":"to keep its operations open for about three weeks ,","depth":10},{"id":199,"text":"notes CRS .","depth":8},{"id":200,"text":"The city now has more autonomy over its budget","depth":8},{"id":201,"text":"and should be able to maintain most of its services ,","depth":9},{"id":202,"text":"despite ties to federal appropriations .","depth":9},{"id":203,"text":"During the 2013 shutdown , city officials had to scramble","depth":9},{"id":204,"text":"to ensure","depth":10},{"id":205,"text":"that DC had the money","depth":11},{"id":206,"text":"it needed","depth":12},{"id":207,"text":"to remain operational ,","depth":12},{"id":208,"text":"but since then , Congress has approved measures","depth":9},{"id":209,"text":"to insulate the impact on the city in the event of a shutdown .","depth":9},{"id":210,"text":"Every agency has its own contingency plan","depth":9},{"id":211,"text":"set up in case of a shutdown ,","depth":9},{"id":212,"text":"and there are a couple of key bodies ,","depth":10},{"id":213,"text":"including the IRS and National Parks ,","depth":10},{"id":214,"text":"that could see some pauses or breaks in service .","depth":9},{"id":215,"text":"Additionally ,","depth":8},{"id":216,"text":"as MarketWatch points out ,","depth":10},{"id":217,"text":"the president has the ability","depth":11},{"id":218,"text":"to determine","depth":12},{"id":219,"text":"whether any service is \" essential \" or not -","depth":12},{"id":220,"text":"so it ' s possible he could try to shut down a key government function like air traffic control","depth":10},{"id":221,"text":"if he really wanted to make a point .","depth":10},{"id":222,"text":"National parks ,","depth":11},{"id":223,"text":"which are funded as part of the Interior Department ,","depth":11},{"id":224,"text":"have long been one of the most visible government entities","depth":11},{"id":225,"text":"affected by a shutdown","depth":11},{"id":226,"text":"and that could happen again this time around .","depth":9},{"id":227,"text":"During last January ' s shutdown , many national parks were still open to visitors ,","depth":10},{"id":228,"text":"but they had limited staffing and closed access to various park facilities ,","depth":11},{"id":229,"text":"including restrooms .","depth":11},{"id":230,"text":"It ' s possible we could see a repeat of this arrangement .","depth":9},{"id":231,"text":"Smithsonian museums and the National Zoo have previously been closed during shutdowns","depth":10},{"id":232,"text":"and would likely be shuttered again","depth":11},{"id":233,"text":"since they derive their funding from the Interior Department .","depth":11},{"id":234,"text":"A key body under the Treasury Department , the IRS has indicated","depth":10},{"id":235,"text":"that it plans to furlough a significant fraction of its workers under a contingency plan ,","depth":11},{"id":236,"text":"since tax season has yet to get underway .","depth":11},{"id":237,"text":"People will still be able to obtain passports and visas ,","depth":10},{"id":238,"text":"although the State Department could stop issuing them","depth":11},{"id":239,"text":"if those services are offered in buildings","depth":12},{"id":240,"text":"run by another agency","depth":13},{"id":241,"text":"that is shut down ,","depth":13},{"id":242,"text":"Bloomberg reports .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":485,"left":372,"right":484,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":372,"left":322,"right":371,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":322,"left":281,"right":321,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":281,"left":265,"right":280,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":265,"left":245,"right":264,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":245,"left":244,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":244,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":264,"left":250,"right":263,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":250,"left":247,"right":249,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":247,"left":3,"right":246,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":246,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":249,"left":6,"right":248,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":248,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":263,"left":255,"right":262,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":255,"left":252,"right":254,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":252,"left":9,"right":251,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":251,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":254,"left":12,"right":253,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent"